cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CL. 

The paper proposes a deep learning method for feature extraction in time-varying signals, specifically in natural video data. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CL (Computation and Language). However, given the focus on deep learning and feature extraction, cs.LG and cs.CV are the most likely categories. The use of a hierarchical generative model and the inference of sparse states also suggest a potential fit with cs.NE and cs.AI. Finally, the application of the model to natural language processing tasks could also make cs.CL a relevant category.
